  "heading": "\\(transitive)::set.theoretic.relation:on{X}",
  "heading_latex": "\\textrm{transitive}\\textrm{ }\\htmlData{mlg-ref=5c7365742e7468656f72657469632e72656c6174696f6e3a6f6e}{\\textrm{relation on }X}",
  "body_text": null,
  "page": null,
  "source": "[\\(transitive)::set.theoretic.relation:on{X}]\nRefines: R\nwhen:\n. X is \\set\nsatisfies:\n. forAll: a, b, c is \\set\n  where:\n  . a \"in\" X\n  . b \"in\" X\n  . c \"in\" X\n  then:\n  . if:\n    . allOf:\n      . \\set.theoretic.ordered.pair:of{a}:and{b} \"in\" R\n      . \\set.theoretic.ordered.pair:of{b}:and{c} \"in\" R\n    then:\n    . \\set.theoretic.ordered.pair:of{a}:and{c} \"in\" R\nDocumented:\n. adjective: \"transitive\"\n. written: \"\\operatorname{transitive}\"\n. description: \"A relation $R$ on $X$ is transitive when $a \\mathbin{R} b$ and $b \\mathbin{R} c$ imply $a \\mathbin{R} c$ for all $a, b, c \\in X$.\"\nId: \"86059ba3-ef94-4bda-96e2-de0256da70e3\"",
